==Dutch==
===Etymology===
{{PIE root|nl|wert}}
From {{inh|nl|dum|werden}}, from {{etyl|odt|nl}} {{m|odt|werthan}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|nl}} {{m|gem-pro|*werþaną}}. Compare German {{term|werden|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|varda|lang=sv}}, obsolete English {{term|worth||to become|lang=en}} and Latin {{term|vertere||turn|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|Nl-worden.ogg|audio|lang=nl}}
* {{IPA|/ˈʋɔr.də(n)/|/ˈwɔr.də(n)/|lang=nl}}

===Verb===
{{nl-verb|werd|geworden}}

# {{context|copulative|lang=nl}} to [[become]]
#: {{ux|nl|Zij wilde altijd al lerares '''worden'''.|She always wanted to become a teacher.|inline=1}}
# {{context|lang=nl|transitive|auxiliary}} Used to form the [[imperfect tense]] of the [[passive voice]], together with a [[past participle]].
#: {{ux|nl|Ze '''worden''' gered.|They are being saved.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|nl|De muur '''werd''' geschilderd.|The wall was being painted.|inline=1}}
#: {{ux|nl|De muur zal '''worden''' geschilderd.|The wall will be painted. / The wall is going to be painted.|inline=1}}

====Usage notes====
* The [[perfect tense]] passive is formed using [[zijn]].

